    "raw_snippet": "World Monitor - Real-Time Global Intelligence Dashboard\nWorld Monitor \u2014 Real-Time Global Intelligence Dashboard\nFree, open-source intelligence platform aggregating live news, markets, military movements, conflicts, and infrastructure into one real-time dashboard. Used by 2M+ people across 190+ countries.\nFeatured in WIRED\n.\nWhat it tracks\nLive conflict events from\nACLED\nand\nUCDP\n, satellite fire detection from\nNASA FIRMS\n, earthquakes from\nUSGS\n, military and civilian aircraft from\nOpenSky Network\n, ship AIS positions from\nAISStream\n, macro and central bank data from\nFRED\n,\nIMF\n, and\nBIS\n, plus 500+ curated RSS feeds, 50+ map layers, and AI-synthesized country briefings.\nFive dashboards, one platform\nWorld Monitor\n\u2014 geopolitics, conflicts, military, infrastructure\nTech Monitor\n\u2014 AI labs, startups, cloud, cybersecurity\nFinance Monitor\n\u2014 global markets, central banks, forex, crypto\nCommodity Monitor\n\u2014 mining, energy, supply chains, freight\nHappy Monitor\n\u2014 positive news, breakthroughs, conservation\nLearn more\nWorld Monitor Pro\n\u2014 AI analyst, personalized digests, MCP for Claude & GPT\nBlog\n\u2014 OSINT guides, geopolitics, market intelligence\nWhat is World Monitor?\nOSINT for everyone \u2014 open-source intelligence democratized\nFive dashboards, one platform \u2014 the variants explained\nOpen source on GitHub (AGPL-3.0)\n\u00d7\nWorld Monitor \u2014 Real-Time Global Intelligence Dashboard\nAI-powered real-time global intelligence dashboard with live news, markets, military tracking, infrastructure monitoring, and geopolitical data. Used by 2M+ people across 190+ countries.\nFeatured in WIRED\n.\nThe platform combines real-time conflict events from\nACLED\nand\nUCDP\n, satellite fire detection from\nNASA FIRMS\n, earthquakes from\nUSGS\n, aircraft tracking from\nOpenSky\n, ship AIS from\nAISStream\n, and macro data from\nFRED\n,\nIMF\n, and\nBIS\n.\nFive dashboards, one platform\nExplore the variant that matches what you track:\nWorld Monitor\nfor geopolitics and conflicts,\nTech Monitor\nfor AI labs and startups,\nFinance Monitor\nfor markets and central banks,\nCommodity Monitor\nfor mining and supply chains, and\nHappy Monitor\nfor positive news and progress.\nRead more\nLearn what the platform does in\nWhat is World Monitor?\n, how OSINT applies in\nOSINT for everyone\n, or compare to traditional tools in\nWorld Monitor vs Bloomberg, Palantir, Dataminr\n. Full source on\nGitHub (AGPL-3.0)\n, or\nupgrade to World Monitor Pro\nfor the AI analyst, custom widget builder, and MCP for Claude and GPT."
  },
